Synopsis:
   shook <hook> <args>

Description:
   SHOOK simulates the hooking of an /ON event with parameters you specify.

Examples:
   /shook msg Me This message is fake
      
   *Me* This message is fake
   
See Also:
   on(4)
   
Other Notes:
   Simulating a hook that depends on $userhost() can cause some major problems
   and confusion in the client. It is advised that you try to avoid that as
   much as possible.

